---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Flora Accessibility"
  description="Accessibility information for Flora Endless Word Search by HSL Innovations."
>
  <section class="page-hero container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility</p>
    <div class="page-app-icon">
        <img
          src="/icons/flora.png"
          alt="Flora app icon"
          class="app-icon"
        />
    </div>
    <h1>Flora Endless Word Search</h1>
    <p>
      Flora is designed to be enjoyable and usable by as many people as possible,
      with accessibility considered throughout the app experience.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card">
    <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
    <p>
      HSL Innovations believes accessibility is part of thoughtful design. Flora
      Endless Word Search is built with clear layouts, readable text, accessible
      controls, and support for Apple accessibility features.
    </p>

    <h2>VoiceOver</h2>
    <p>
      Flora includes VoiceOver support to help players navigate and understand
      the puzzle interface.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Grid cells announce their row, column, and letter.</li>
      <li>Selected cells provide feedback when chosen.</li>
      <li>Found words are communicated through accessible state information.</li>
      <li>Toolbar buttons use descriptive labels such as Back, New, and Help.</li>
      <li>Celebration screens present meaningful completion information.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Dynamic Type</h2>
    <p>
      Flora supports larger text sizes using Apple's Dynamic Type settings.
      Players who increase text size in iOS or iPadOS should see improved
      readability across instructions, buttons, word lists, and game screens.
    </p>

    <h2>Color and Contrast</h2>
    <p>
      Flora is designed for readability in both Light Mode and Dark Mode. The app
      uses system colors where appropriate so text, backgrounds, and interface
      elements adapt to the user's appearance settings.
    </p>

    <p>
      Word selections and completed words use visual state changes to help make
      progress easier to understand during gameplay.
    </p>

    <h2>Dark Mode</h2>
    <p>
      Flora supports both Light Appearance and Dark Appearance and follows the
      user's system setting automatically.
    </p>

    <h2>Haptic Feedback</h2>
    <p>
      On supported Apple devices, Flora uses subtle haptic feedback to confirm
      actions such as finding a word and completing a puzzle.
    </p>

    <p>
      Devices that do not include haptic hardware will continue to work normally;
      haptic feedback simply will not be felt on those devices.
    </p>

    <h2>Device Support</h2>
    <p>
      Flora is designed for iPhone and iPad, with layouts that adapt to different
      screen sizes and orientations. On iPad, landscape layouts provide more room
      for the puzzle grid and word list.
    </p>

    <h2>Ongoing Improvements</h2>
    <p>
      Accessibility is an ongoing effort. Future updates may improve VoiceOver
      navigation, layout behavior, text scaling, contrast, and other parts of the
      experience based on testing and user feedback.
    </p>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>
      If you encounter an accessibility issue or have suggestions for improving
      Flora, please contact HSL Innovations through the <a href="/support"> Support page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
